  {
    "id": "591f5848-54c",
    "phase": 1,
    "category": "pitfall",
    "severity": "critical",
    "lesson": "P0-1: Design described \"lazy retirement on read\" for score_decayed entries but never specified the write-back step. getGlobalLessons() would mark entries retired in memory but never persist the change, creating phantom pool occupants that block new entries forever. Root cause: designer focused on the read path (filter retired) without tracing the write path (persist retirement marks).",
    "context": "Design review v1 found getGlobalLessons() missing writeAtomic() after retirement pass. Fixed in v2 by adding explicit persist step. This is a classic \"read-modify but forget to write\" pattern in lazy evaluation designs.",
    "topic": "lessons-evolution",
    "reusable": true,
    "appliedCount": 28,
